Richostein 2025-12-22 04:53 p.m.
MINUTE ORDER: The Court has reviewed the written Plea Agreement. The Court finds that the Defendant is competent, and that the plea is entered knowingly. ORDERED that the plea agreement is ACCEPTED by the Court. The Defendants plea of nolo contendere to Counts Nine through Thirteen is ACCEPTED AND ENTERED. Upon motion of the People of the State of Mayflower, Counts One through Eight are DISMISSED with prejudice pursuant to the plea bargain. Based upon the Defendants plea of nolo contendere, the Court enters a judgment of conviction on Counts Nine through Thirteen, without any admission of factual guilt by the Defendant. The Defendant is sentenced to a three (3) month conditional discharge, subject to the following conditions: (a) restitution, of $130,000 UCD. Any monies paid for a contempt order will be reimposed by this Court, (b) fefendant shall not order, direct, solicit, receive, or permit the transmission of any monetary payments arising from any civil or criminal contempt proceeding to the Defendants personal benefit or personal bank account, directly or indirectly, (c) the Defendant shall immediately recuse himself from any judicial proceedings arising from the contempt matters at issue and shall withdraw or nullify any related directives or communications previously issued. The Court retains continuing jurisdiction during the conditional discharge period to enforce all terms and conditions. In the event of non-compliance, the Court may impose any sentence authorized by law. District Judge Richostein (Signed: 12/22/2025)(edited)
